  "prompt": "What are the various Incarnations of Lord Vishnu and what is going to be the last Incarnation of Lord Vishnu?",
  "response": "Lord Vishnu, one of the principal deities of Hinduism, is said to have ten primary incarnations known as the Dashavatara. These incarnations are believed to have descended to earth at various times to restore cosmic order. Here are the ten avatars:\n\n1. **Matsya** (The Fish) - Saved the sacred scriptures and humanity from a great flood.\n2. **Kurma** (The Tortoise) - Provided a base for Mount Mandara during the churning of the ocean.\n3. **Varaha** (The Boar) - Rescued the Earth (personified as the goddess Bhudevi) from the demon Hiranyaksha.\n4. **Narasimha** (The Man-Lion) - Destroyed the demon Hiranyakashipu to protect his devotee Prahlada.\n5. **Vamana** (The Dwarf) - Subdued the demon king Bali by asking for three paces of land and expanding to cover the universe.\n6. **Parashurama** (The Warrior with an Axe) - Eradicated corrupt Kshatriya warriors to restore dharma.\n7. **Rama** (The Prince of Ayodhya) - The protagonist of the Ramayana, who defeated the demon king Ravana.\n8. **Krishna** (The Divine Statesman) - A central figure in the Mahabharata and spiritual guide in the Bhagavad Gita.\n9. **Buddha** (The Enlightened One) - Considered by some traditions as an avatar who came to teach compassion and non-violence.\n10. **Kalki** (The Warrior with a Sword) - The prophesied future incarnation who is expected to appear at the end of the current Kali Yuga to restore righteousness.\n\nThe last incarnation, Kalki, is yet to come and is believed to end the current age of darkness and corruption, known as Kali Yuga, by vanquishing evil forces and restoring dharma, paving the way for a new cycle of time.",
